dc:creator><![CDATA[angelinesg7]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Truth</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/s9XppW4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JZIP2ir.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/s9XppW4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[angelinesg7]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Qe4QR6i</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/792PthJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Qe4QR6i</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[memento757]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Cake day field day!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/dYfAVjA</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/V9MJoLL.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Ok it's not my imgur cake day but it IS my business cake day! 8 years ago TODAY I put it all on the line, quit my job, and started a craft business. I had nearly no idea what I was doing when I started but here I still stand after a divorce, several moves, and a pandemic.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/o01bpIt.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I spend most of my days wrestling large blocks of coconut oil, mounds of beeswax, 5 gallon pails of oils, and pouring endless balms and candles. It's really the best way to spend my time.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XzIEC1L.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Every day I'm labelin'

I do every part of every task as I am the whole company. I ship every order, build every craft show booth + tear it down, run the sales, ship the orders, prep and make and clean up for production, take the photos and the videos etc...</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hj10Jox.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And pouring.

So much pouring- I LOVE pouring candles and balm. It quiets my mind as my entire body attends to the task at hand. My worries cease, my steady hands know what to do- the completed task is immensely satisfying, every time.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/z9M2tH4.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Finished product! Yay!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4669VQU.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>LIP BALMS are so effing POPULAR. I sell around 500 lip balms every month meaning I'm at this task nearly every week keeping all 8 varieties in stock. Ingredients are coconut oil, sunflower oil, beeswax, and essential oils.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/y3oLkAh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>When I finish all that making, I head to my island market and set up my booth! My happy place!

Link is in my bio for interested imgurians.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ycGN2Ak.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Cat tax: SOUND ON to hear Jerry say hello!

Stay weird, imgur.

And now, with two requests on file in the comments, here is my shop link: www.rachelmadeproducts.com 

Thanks for the love, imgur. You guys really are the heckin' BEST.

TO ALL MY PEOPLE IN NEED OF CAKE (apologies for my unintentionally deceptive title)- here's my German chocolate cupcake recipe I posted for my imgur cake day last year: 
